8T18:49:30.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/354335832","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/567518?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/haroldiedema","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU2NzUxOA==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"haroldiedema","type":"User","id":567518,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema\/orgs"}},{"index":12,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"I've never been a big fan of that API style (passing an object to the constructor). It's error prone and a hard to maintain (and you need constants).\r\n\r\nI would have gone with something like this:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nlet material = new THREE.MeshPhongMaterial().setBackSide();\r\n```","created_at":"2017-12-28T18:53:22.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/12972#issuecomment-354336559","id":354336559,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12972","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM1NDMzNjU1OQ==","updated_at":"2017-12-28T18:54:41.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/354336559","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":13,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"I agree. But I'd rather solve this in an API using \"data objects\", to maintain backward compatibility and allow custom frameworks to configure THREE 'classes' in an easy manner.\r\n\r\nSomething like this:\r\n```javascript\r\nclass PhongMaterialDefinition extends Object\r\n{\r\n    setColor (color)\r\n    {\r\n        this.color = color; \/\/ Could do additional type-checking here.\r\n        return this;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    setFrontSide ()\r\n    {\r\n        this.side = THREE.FrontSide;\r\n        return this;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    setBackSide ()\r\n    {\r\n        this.side = THREE.BackSide;\r\n        return this;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nlet my_definition = new PhongMaterialDefinition()\r\n    .setColor(0xff00ff)\r\n    .setFrontSide();\r\n\r\nlet my_material = new THREE.MeshPhongMaterial(my_definition);\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis way, the current implementation still works and allows IDE's for showing autocompletion on all available parameters for said definitions.\r\n\r\nDon't start with maintainability of this approach, I know \ud83d\ude06 ","created_at":"2017-12-28T18:58:21.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/12972#issuecomment-354337829","id":354337829,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12972","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM1NDMzNzgyOQ==","updated_at":"2017-12-28T19:01:22.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/354337829","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/567518?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/haroldiedema","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU2NzUxOA==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"haroldiedema","type":"User","id":567518,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema\/orgs"}},{"index":14,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"I miss somethings about the deprecation here. \r\n\r\n@mrdoob you're saying that all stuff in legacy will never be removed ? What is the goal to mark some function deprecated in a certain build if it is not to remove them in the next ???\r\n\r\nPeople that already use constant stuff use a certain build version like r88 for example. If they want to upgrade their code base they will upgrade the three version to r89 and so got the deprecation warnings. They will upgrade what is marked as deprecated. \r\nAnd finally the deprecated stuff could be remove under r90, considering that their code base is already upgraded. So no breaking can happen ?!\r\n\r\n@donmccurdy \r\n\r\n> THREE.CullFace.NONE\r\n\r\nYes i think it is more readable, i will change to this.\r\n\r\nAbout:\r\n\r\n> renderer.setFrontFaceCulling( boolean );\r\nrenderer.setBackFaceCulling( boolean );\r\n\r\nUsing a bool is not necessary, but using function instead of simple integral constants, will increase the code base, the code complexity (IMO), and won't be easily shareable between classes. Imagine a class with 3-4 constants of 3 or 4 member each... So 9 to 16 methods to add, documents etc... ??? Uuuhhh....\r\n\r\nHowever, chainable call could be a great thing in three, i remember a try for Three.App with @looeee using such things.\r\n","created_at":"2017-12-28T19:38:35.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/12972#issuecomment-354345488","id":354345488,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12972","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM1NDM0NTQ4OA==","updated_at":"2017-12-28T19:38:35.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/354345488","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Itee\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Itee\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/5276909?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Itee","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Itee\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Itee","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Itee\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjUyNzY5MDk=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Itee\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Itee\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Itee\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"Itee","type":"User","id":5276909,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Itee\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.git