72","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM1NzI3OTkzNQ==","updated_at":"2018-01-12T16:08:10.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/357279935","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/567518?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/haroldiedema","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU2NzUxOA==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"haroldiedema","type":"User","id":567518,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/haroldiedema\/orgs"}},{"index":18,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"I agree it's good practice, but I don't think that's what people do \ud83d\ude15","created_at":"2018-01-12T20:56:51.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/12972#issuecomment-357351782","id":357351782,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12972","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM1NzM1MTc4Mg==","updated_at":"2018-01-12T20:56:51.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/357351782","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":19,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"Yes, they should upgrades incrementally, and in this way we could 'safely' remove legacy stuff after some releases.\r\n\r\nKeep backward compatibility for older browser ( that are still supported by their producer, but don't make backward compatibility for ie7 for example ) is good\/required.\r\n\r\nBut keep legacy stuff along the complete live of a library is, IMO, a non sens. \r\n\r\nThe problem here about the update is that people are not award about when could happen breaking change when they upgrade. No Major version upgrade. That normally signal to end user that some things will break.\r\n\r\nThe good idea could be to keep legacy stuff between 2 major version. \r\n\r\nFor example:\r\n\r\nr89 -> 1.0.0: current legacy stuff still here.\r\n1.0.0 -> 1.1.12: current legacy stuff still here + new legacy stuff about 1.0.0+\r\n1.1.23 -> 2.0.0: legacy stuff from r89 removed, new legacy about 1.0.0+ still here\r\netc...\r\n\r\nThis allow people to don't see application break between major release, if they upgrade incrementally major version. That is, in fact, like does almost all packages, so people should be aware about this type of practices during their development life (even if they are new comer).\r\n\r\n","created_at":"2018-01-13T09:07:37.000Z","ht